      <p class="comment__time">3 months 1 week ago</p>
                    <p class="visually-hidden">In reply to <a href="/comment/136890#comment-136890" class="permalink" rel="bookmark" hreflang="en">Love Farmers Almanac……my…</a> by <span>Ollie Kovaluk (not verified)</span></p>
          </footer>
    <div class="comment__content">
      
            <div class="text-content field field--name-comment-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item comment__text-content"><p>Hi, Ollie. There are several things you can do: choose resistant varieties (such as ‘Chieftan’ and ‘Elba’); try to maintain soil pH between 5.0 and 5.2 (you can decrease soil pH by adding elemental sulfur); dust seed potatoes with sulfur before planting; use pine needle mulch; keep soil moist after tubers start to form; and do not use&nbsp;manure.</p></div>
      <ul class="links inline comment__links">
          <li class="comment__links-item"><a href="/comment/reply/node/90268/comment_node_plant/136895" class="comment__links-link">Reply</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
</div></div>
    <div class="views-row">
