<div class="indented">
<article  data-comment-user-id="343787" id="comment-133643" class="comment" role="article" data-drupal-selector="comment">
  <div class="comment__text-wrapper">
    <footer class="comment__meta">
      <p class="comment__author"><a title="View user profile." href="/author/editors">The Editors</a></p>
      <p class="comment__time">1 year 1 month ago</p>
                    <p class="visually-hidden">In reply to <a href="/comment/133631#comment-133631" class="permalink" rel="bookmark" hreflang="en">I was not able to harvest my…</a> by <span>Mary Pelcher (not verified)</span></p>
          </footer>
    <div class="comment__content">
      
            <div class="text-content field field--name-comment-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item comment__text-content"><p>Hi, Mary. If you live in a place where the ground does not freeze over in the winter, your potatoes likely continued to grow and will now be crowded and small. When you dig them up, check to make sure they are not green and that the skin is still&nbsp;firm.&nbsp;</p></div>
      <ul class="links inline comment__links">
          <li class="comment__links-item"><a href="/comment/reply/node/90268/comment_node_plant/133643" class="comment__links-link">Reply</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
