    <div class="views-row">
<div class="indented">
<article  data-comment-user-id="343787" id="comment-131561" class="comment" role="article" data-drupal-selector="comment">
  <div class="comment__text-wrapper">
    <footer class="comment__meta">
      <p class="comment__author"><a title="View user profile." href="/author/editors">The Editors</a></p>
      <p class="comment__time">1 year 7 months ago</p>
                    <p class="visually-hidden">In reply to <a href="/comment/131554#comment-131554" class="permalink" rel="bookmark" hreflang="en">I plant Russets but my…</a> by <span>Mark Keith  (not verified)</span></p>
          </footer>
    <div class="comment__content">
      
            <div class="text-content field field--name-comment-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item comment__text-content"><p>Hi, Mark. Was your entire crop of potatoes very small? It is not unusual for potatoes to vary in size and to have some large, some medium, and some small ones. If they were all small, it was probably a water issue which could be that alternate wet and dry conditions stunted their growth. Potatoes prefer evenly moist&nbsp;conditions.</p></div>
      <ul class="links inline comment__links">
          <li class="comment__links-item"><a href="/comment/reply/node/90268/comment_node_plant/131561" class="comment__links-link">Reply</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
